Multilevel Inheritance

> A class inherits from a class that is itself inherited from another class.

Structure:

Animal â†’ Dog â†’ Puppy

ðŸ”¸ Code:

class Animal:
    def sound(self):
        print("Animal makes sound")

class Dog(Animal):
    def bark(self):
        print("Dog barks")

class Puppy(Dog):
    def weep(self):
        print("Puppy weeps")

p = Puppy()
p.sound()  # From Animal
p.bark()   # From Dog
p.weep()   # From Puppy

ðŸ–¨ï¸ Output:

Animal makes sound
Dog barks
Puppy weeps


---

2ï¸âƒ£ Hierarchical Inheritance

> Multiple child classes inherit from the same parent class.



ðŸ“Š Structure:

Person
        /    \
    Student  Teacher

ðŸ”¸ Code:

class Person:
    def details(self):
        print("I am a person")

class Student(Person):
    def study(self):
        print("I am studying")

class Teacher(Person):
    def teach(self):
        print("I am teaching")

s = Student()
t = Teacher()

s.details()  # From Person
s.study()    # Own

t.details()  # From Person
t.teach()    # Own

ðŸ–¨ï¸ Output:

I am a person
I am studying
I am a person
I am teaching


---

3ï¸âƒ£ Hybrid Inheritance

> Combination of more than one type of inheritance (like multiple + multilevel).



ðŸ“Š Structure:

Person
       /      \
   Student   Teacher
       \      /
      Assistant

ðŸ”¸ Code:

class Person:
    def info(self):
        print("I am a person")

class Student(Person):
    def learn(self):
        print("I am learning")

class Teacher(Person):
    def teach(self):
        print("I am teaching")

class Assistant(Student, Teacher):
    def assist(self):
        print("I assist both")

a = Assistant()
a.info()    # From Person
a.learn()   # From Student
a.teach()   # From Teacher
a.assist()  # Own method

ðŸ–¨ï¸ Output:

I am a person
I am learning
I am teaching
I assist both

> âœ… Python uses Method Resolution Order (MRO) to resolve conflicts in hybrid inheritance.


